WEBVTT

00:00:00.117 --> 00:00:01.587
If you don't incorporate my feedback,

00:00:02.032 --> 00:00:03.832
I'm not approving the design.

00:00:05.332 --> 00:00:06.602
I'm not doing it.

00:00:08.042 --> 00:00:09.802
I'm the client, and you're refusing my request?

00:00:11.472 --> 00:00:13.212
You're unbelievable.

00:00:13.512 --> 00:00:15.742
I'm telling you I'm fine,

00:00:16.112 --> 00:00:18.752
so why do you have a problem with it? Why?

00:00:18.982 --> 00:00:20.482
Seriously, what is your deal?

00:00:20.552 --> 00:00:23.222
I don't know. I don't know why I'm doing this.

00:00:23.382 --> 00:00:24.822
I guess I must like you.

00:00:30.122 --> 00:00:31.122
So?

00:00:32.192 --> 00:00:33.562
So, what will you do about it?

00:00:34.902 --> 00:00:37.502
What? Are you going to ask me out or something?

00:00:38.402 --> 00:00:39.632
Dream on.

00:00:41.242 --> 00:00:42.902
You need to sort out your feelings on your own, you know?

00:00:45.142 --> 00:00:46.172
So she knew?

00:00:49.482 --> 00:00:50.782
I'm going to step out for a minute.

00:00:51.252 --> 00:00:52.582
Pull yourself together while I'm gone.

00:01:02.022 --> 00:01:04.732
(Jung Hyeon Su Architecture Lab)

00:01:05.892 --> 00:01:08.102
Of all the stunts to pull. Seriously.

00:01:11.232 --> 00:01:13.532
Does he realise how many times he's caught me off guard?

00:01:13.532 --> 00:01:14.702
I guess he figured if he said that,

00:01:14.772 --> 00:01:18.072
I'd be flustered and speechless. Unbelievable.

00:01:19.472 --> 00:01:21.612
And why is he sticking his nose into my nap room?

00:01:22.312 --> 00:01:25.112
When is he going to drop that whole "I'm your senior" act?

00:01:32.452 --> 00:01:33.852
Lee Ji Hyuk, you crazy fool.

00:01:36.362 --> 00:01:37.762
I guess I must like you.

00:01:38.332 --> 00:01:39.992
You need to sort out your feelings on your own, you know?

00:01:42.502 --> 00:01:43.732
So it was that obvious.

00:01:44.562 --> 00:01:46.102
And I thought I was hiding it so well.

00:01:47.072 --> 00:01:48.472
But still,

00:01:49.142 --> 00:01:51.612
how could she shut me down like that in a split second?

00:01:52.612 --> 00:01:54.612
I knew it would never work out anyway.

00:01:54.982 --> 00:01:56.242
Never make that mistake again.

00:01:57.012 --> 00:01:58.752
Just stick to work.

00:02:05.552 --> 00:02:06.922
How am I going to smooth this over?

00:02:18.502 --> 00:02:19.932
Oh, hey.

00:02:19.932 --> 00:02:22.872
Take the blueprints and review them. I'll get your feedback tomorrow.

00:02:23.942 --> 00:02:25.872
And don't tell me what to do with my own personal space.

00:02:26.672 --> 00:02:29.312
Just mark down anything you want to add or revise.

00:02:31.382 --> 00:02:32.382
All right.

00:02:52.032 --> 00:02:53.532
She won't even hear me out.

00:02:54.332 --> 00:02:56.872
I was nice to you because you lived and worked hard.

00:02:57.472 --> 00:02:58.472
Remember your place.

00:02:59.642 --> 00:03:03.142
Stay away. I don't have to give someone a chance...

00:03:04.382 --> 00:03:05.982
if I don't think they suit me.

00:03:07.482 --> 00:03:08.482
Do I, Eun Oh?

00:03:11.052 --> 00:03:12.122
Is she throwing it back in my face?

00:03:13.152 --> 00:03:16.722
So she knew I liked her all along and was just pretending she didn't?

00:03:18.792 --> 00:03:19.792
I'm losing my mind.

00:03:22.662 --> 00:03:23.662
Son.

00:03:26.032 --> 00:03:27.432
By the way, lately...

00:03:28.042 --> 00:03:30.772
Are you and Ji Hyuk having one? A war of nerves.

00:03:31.072 --> 00:03:32.072
Oh, please.

00:03:32.642 --> 00:03:35.112
What father has a war of nerves with his son?

00:03:35.382 --> 00:03:37.612
I'm just really upset with Ji Hyuk, that's all.

00:03:38.412 --> 00:03:41.052
Don't give me that. Honestly.

00:03:42.022 --> 00:03:43.752
Fathers and sons.

00:03:43.752 --> 00:03:46.192
It's always man to man. That's just how it is.

00:03:47.322 --> 00:03:50.022
It was like that when you grew up, and I've seen it all over.

00:03:50.622 --> 00:03:53.932
Once a son becomes a man, they both try not to back down.

00:03:53.992 --> 00:03:55.662
That's what a war of nerves is.

00:03:56.132 --> 00:03:59.032
I was never like that with my own father.

00:03:59.402 --> 00:04:01.402
Oh, please. Of course, you were.

00:04:02.772 --> 00:04:04.472
Whenever your father would say something,

00:04:04.742 --> 00:04:06.472
you'd say, "I'll handle it myself."

00:04:07.012 --> 00:04:09.542
Then your father would fly off the handle,

00:04:09.812 --> 00:04:13.552
and then you two wouldn't speak to each other for over two weeks.

00:04:14.712 --> 00:04:16.382
Well, back then,

00:04:17.052 --> 00:04:18.922
it was probably because Dad was being unreasonable.

00:04:21.692 --> 00:04:23.322
But now...

00:04:24.062 --> 00:04:25.892
You're the father now, aren't you?

00:04:26.662 --> 00:04:29.132
How can a parent ever win against their own child?

00:04:30.602 --> 00:04:34.072
Why does a parent always have to be the one to give in?

00:04:34.532 --> 00:04:36.442
No, it's not about winning.

00:04:36.872 --> 00:04:41.542
He's 33 now. He's old enough to know better,

00:04:41.642 --> 00:04:45.812
but he insists he's always right. I should discipline him.

00:04:46.482 --> 00:04:47.582
Oh, good grief.

00:04:48.652 --> 00:04:51.322
I guess it's true what they say about fathers and sons being beasts.

00:05:00.692 --> 00:05:01.762
You're back already.

00:05:02.862 --> 00:05:03.862
Yes, because of your grandma.

00:05:03.862 --> 00:05:05.902
I had a feeling you'd come home because of her.

00:05:06.432 --> 00:05:07.602
So you didn't leave after all?

00:05:08.302 --> 00:05:09.802
I told you I wasn't leaving.

00:05:09.902 --> 00:05:13.442
I know, you brat. Of course, you're brazen enough to stay.

00:05:15.812 --> 00:05:16.812
Ji Hyuk.

00:05:17.242 --> 00:05:19.052
What brings you home so early?

00:05:19.652 --> 00:05:20.682
Because of Father.

00:05:22.052 --> 00:05:23.382
You were right.

00:05:24.022 --> 00:05:26.022
- Have you eaten? - Not yet.

00:05:26.092 --> 00:05:27.222
Okay.

00:05:27.552 --> 00:05:29.292
It's about time my son got a home-cooked meal.

00:05:29.592 --> 00:05:32.092
- Go wash up. I'll set the table. - Okay.

00:05:32.662 --> 00:05:36.362
What, does he not have hands? Tell him to make his own dinner.

00:05:36.732 --> 00:05:38.172
Mom, it's okay. I'll get it myself.

00:05:42.602 --> 00:05:43.702
Just go wash up.

00:05:48.512 --> 00:05:50.512
It's that soy-braised pork Dad loves.

00:05:53.012 --> 00:05:54.282
Oh, it's good.

00:05:56.722 --> 00:05:57.882
What is it? Do you need something?

00:05:59.192 --> 00:06:00.192
Mom.

00:06:00.892 --> 00:06:02.192
Why aren't you saying anything?

00:06:03.492 --> 00:06:04.562
About what?

00:06:05.292 --> 00:06:06.832
You must have your own take on this, right?

00:06:07.332 --> 00:06:10.002
Like telling me to apologise to Father or something?

00:06:10.862 --> 00:06:11.872
No.

00:06:12.732 --> 00:06:15.572
I don't know exactly why your father's acting this way,

00:06:15.772 --> 00:06:17.872
and frankly, I don't know why you are either.

00:06:18.772 --> 00:06:21.982
Since I don't know the whole story, how can I tell you two what to do?

00:06:22.412 --> 00:06:23.682
You two sort it out yourselves.

00:06:24.342 --> 00:06:25.352
Just...

00:06:25.682 --> 00:06:27.682
don't go raising your voices in the house.

00:06:29.582 --> 00:06:30.582
I'll try to be careful.

00:06:31.752 --> 00:06:32.892
By the way, Ji Hyuk...

00:06:33.952 --> 00:06:36.522
Let's just drop the whole thing about living expenses.

00:06:36.962 --> 00:06:37.962
Come on, Mom.

00:06:38.262 --> 00:06:40.692
I agree with your father on that.

00:06:41.032 --> 00:06:43.902
So let's not talk about it anymore.

00:06:44.502 --> 00:06:46.172
Fine. For now.

00:06:46.902 --> 00:06:48.772
Ji Hyuk, you got home early.

00:06:49.502 --> 00:06:52.012
I saw Dad's shoes by the door. Is he home too?

00:06:52.572 --> 00:06:53.942
Yes, he's in his room.

00:06:54.542 --> 00:06:56.312
So, Ji Hyuk was totally right.

00:06:56.642 --> 00:06:57.882
How did he guess that?

00:06:58.952 --> 00:07:00.012
Dad!

00:07:00.312 --> 00:07:01.782
The nerve of that kid...

00:07:02.452 --> 00:07:03.822
"I knew you'd be back?"

00:07:04.182 --> 00:07:07.292
What does he know, acting so smug? That brat.

00:07:08.892 --> 00:07:10.662
- Dad. - Yes, hey.

00:07:10.662 --> 00:07:11.762
I'm home.

00:07:13.462 --> 00:07:17.462
Dad, where did you sleep last night? Do you know how worried I was?

00:07:18.332 --> 00:07:19.472
I'm sorry about that.

00:07:19.932 --> 00:07:22.602
Next time you have a fight like that, make sure I'm home.

00:07:22.872 --> 00:07:24.972
I'll kick Ji Hyuk out for you.

00:07:25.242 --> 00:07:27.972
Oh, sweetie. What could you do? You silly kid.

00:07:35.522 --> 00:07:39.022
Three units left at Hyunmyeong Apts, with no defect claims so far.

00:07:39.152 --> 00:07:41.422
We've started on five units at the Ohyang Apartments,

00:07:41.792 --> 00:07:44.122
and we're prepping for construction on 27 homes at Yeonseong Apartments.

00:07:45.092 --> 00:07:46.562
What's the status on our hiring search?

00:07:47.292 --> 00:07:49.162
The application deadline is this week,

00:07:49.162 --> 00:07:50.502
and interviews are next week,

00:07:51.102 --> 00:07:53.272
but individual contracts are flooding in.

00:07:53.272 --> 00:07:55.272
We need to hire a site manager first.

00:07:56.942 --> 00:07:58.342
When would you like to meet?

00:08:03.542 --> 00:08:05.882
(Ji Eun Oh)

00:08:05.982 --> 00:08:07.212
(I want a mini-showroom with an open layout.)

00:08:07.282 --> 00:08:08.582
(The materials list will be sent today.)

00:08:08.652 --> 00:08:10.452
I want a mini-showroom with an open layout,

00:08:10.452 --> 00:08:12.122
so the staff can move around and work comfortably.

00:08:12.652 --> 00:08:14.752
The materials list will be sent today.

00:08:16.992 --> 00:08:18.562
I asked to set up a meeting, and this is what I get?

00:08:19.692 --> 00:08:22.432
He's so ridiculously fickle. It's unforgivable.

00:08:23.302 --> 00:08:25.002
He's the one who let it slip.

00:08:32.072 --> 00:08:34.142
Oh? Ms. Ji.

00:08:34.712 --> 00:08:35.782
Hello.

00:08:36.182 --> 00:08:39.082
Good timing. I was about to send you Lee Ri Na and Kim Ji Seon's...

00:08:39.082 --> 00:08:41.722
- final turnkey project plans. - I see.

00:08:42.222 --> 00:08:44.522
I'm actually here to meet with Mr. Lee.

00:08:45.692 --> 00:08:47.852
I sent you a text about that.

00:08:47.922 --> 00:08:51.122
I'm having lunch with the staff today.

00:08:52.262 --> 00:08:53.492
Then I'll just join you.

00:09:02.072 --> 00:09:04.002
Cheol Min, you want to grab lunch with us?

00:09:05.972 --> 00:09:08.682
I avoid the lunch rush. It's always too packed.

00:09:17.522 --> 00:09:21.192
I have that lunch meeting with the newly signed coordinators.

00:09:21.192 --> 00:09:22.362
I told you, remember?

00:09:26.192 --> 00:09:28.662
- Was that today? - Yes.

00:09:29.702 --> 00:09:32.602
I guess Mr. Lee is so busy, he must've mixed up the dates.

00:09:34.002 --> 00:09:35.102
I guess it's just you and me, then.

00:09:44.942 --> 00:09:47.952
No one's in the elevator. And it's lunchtime.

00:09:49.252 --> 00:09:50.282
Right!

00:09:50.582 --> 00:09:51.992
So, I was thinking...

00:09:52.452 --> 00:09:53.952
About the mini-showroom.

00:09:54.322 --> 00:09:56.722
You want an open layout for the staff to...

00:10:05.062 --> 00:10:06.832
Let's talk when we get to the restaurant.

00:10:08.372 --> 00:10:10.342
Oh, sure.

00:10:12.642 --> 00:10:13.642
I'm starving.

00:10:15.282 --> 00:10:16.412
Aren't you hungry?

00:10:20.852 --> 00:10:21.852
- At company dinners... - The stew is always...

00:10:22.052 --> 00:10:26.192
For the mini-showroom, how many staff tables go in the open space?

00:10:26.352 --> 00:10:30.022
And for that to happen, tell me what materials you'll display.

00:10:30.622 --> 00:10:33.962
- Oh, I got it. - Have some water first.

00:10:34.292 --> 00:10:35.532
You need to take a breath.

00:10:36.362 --> 00:10:39.632
You seem so busy. Too busy to even have a meeting.

00:10:40.772 --> 00:10:44.072
Right, that's my point. We could've just chatted about this.

00:10:44.502 --> 00:10:46.912
For something under an hour in person?

00:10:48.072 --> 00:10:51.212
How do I explain the layout by text? Never mind.

00:10:51.382 --> 00:10:53.782
The mini-showroom will have a sink.

00:10:53.782 --> 00:10:55.922
Windows, flooring, wallpaper, wall molding,

00:10:55.982 --> 00:10:57.382
tiles, finishing films, bathroom fixtures...

00:10:58.022 --> 00:10:59.192
Are you going to include all of that?

00:11:01.392 --> 00:11:04.662
- Isn't it too small for all that? - Exactly.

00:11:04.822 --> 00:11:08.662
I was taking my time to figure out which materials to prioritise.

00:11:08.802 --> 00:11:11.062
But without that list,

00:11:11.162 --> 00:11:14.002
I can't even start on the mini-showroom design.

00:11:14.632 --> 00:11:17.272
- Here's your food. - Thank you.

00:11:18.402 --> 00:11:19.442
Thank you.

00:11:19.742 --> 00:11:21.212
Enjoy your meal.

00:11:21.812 --> 00:11:23.782
Let's eat first, and then we can talk. Okay?

00:11:23.912 --> 00:11:26.482
Let's talk while we eat. Since you're so busy.

00:11:29.722 --> 00:11:34.622
So, why do you want an open-plan space for your team?

00:11:35.992 --> 00:11:39.092
I hate being stuck in an office all day, just working.

00:11:40.532 --> 00:11:42.502
Instead of a separate office,

00:11:42.502 --> 00:11:45.232
why not keep the current cafe layout?

00:11:45.402 --> 00:11:47.632
Come on, that'd be way too open.

00:11:48.202 --> 00:11:50.372
What positions are you hiring for?

00:11:51.242 --> 00:11:53.172
A site manager...

00:11:53.612 --> 00:11:55.542
and a staff member dedicated to Mamdaerozip.

00:11:56.082 --> 00:11:57.342
Perfect.

00:11:57.742 --> 00:12:01.182
Cheol Min is always there, right? And Mr. Jo, too.

00:12:01.282 --> 00:12:02.952
The site manager will be out a lot,

00:12:02.952 --> 00:12:05.082
and the staff member will be on the phone frequently.

00:12:06.292 --> 00:12:10.492
Put six desks by the break room wall and use bookshelves as dividers.

00:12:10.562 --> 00:12:12.962
And keep the cafe layout for the rest of the space.

00:12:13.492 --> 00:12:14.692
Oh, I see.

00:12:15.062 --> 00:12:16.832
- So, basically. - Okay, let's just eat first.

00:12:16.832 --> 00:12:18.632
My noodles are getting soggy. I'm starving.

00:12:27.812 --> 00:12:29.842
Hey, slow down a little.

00:12:34.882 --> 00:12:36.222
Just listen while you eat.

00:12:36.752 --> 00:12:37.922
My point is...

00:12:38.222 --> 00:12:41.092
This way, we'll save on construction costs,

00:12:41.152 --> 00:12:43.992
and the construction timeline gets much shorter.

00:12:44.422 --> 00:12:47.562
Okay, fine! We'll do it your way. Now, let's just eat.

00:12:48.762 --> 00:12:52.102
Really? So nothing else will change, right?

00:12:52.172 --> 00:12:53.172
Yes.

00:12:53.672 --> 00:12:54.872
Now, let's eat.

00:13:26.202 --> 00:13:28.742
I almost wish Seong Jae would just make his move already.

00:13:34.142 --> 00:13:36.882
(Action Plan)

00:13:38.912 --> 00:13:40.652
Is this the same Lee Ji Hyuk I know?

00:13:43.352 --> 00:13:45.322
Mamdaerozip Version 2.0...

00:13:46.822 --> 00:13:49.192
plus a comprehensive materials showroom?

00:13:51.962 --> 00:13:52.962
My gosh.

00:13:57.062 --> 00:13:59.872
Mr. Park, the buyer from Italy is here.

00:14:01.072 --> 00:14:02.142
Okay, got it.

00:14:06.942 --> 00:14:09.782
I understand that other show companies...

00:14:09.782 --> 00:14:11.942
were also under consideration.

00:14:13.082 --> 00:14:17.052
Could you share the reason why our company was chosen?

00:14:24.162 --> 00:14:26.992
Because of him, Mr. Park Seong Jae.

00:14:27.892 --> 00:14:29.562
Mr. Ferrari, nice to see you again.

00:14:29.632 --> 00:14:30.632
Great to see you.

00:14:34.902 --> 00:14:36.002
Now, please...

00:14:43.282 --> 00:14:45.182
The shoes are very comfortable, aren't they?

00:14:45.342 --> 00:14:48.382
They are, but...

00:14:48.452 --> 00:14:51.252
Are these all the designs you currently offer?

00:14:51.882 --> 00:14:55.562
We were expecting designs that are more unique.

00:14:55.622 --> 00:14:58.762
With more personality.

00:15:00.162 --> 00:15:04.362
Our Shoe Joy products have more strength in functionality.

00:15:05.832 --> 00:15:06.832
Okay.

00:15:15.442 --> 00:15:16.742
Have you seen everything?

00:15:17.682 --> 00:15:19.252
Yes, roughly.

00:15:20.252 --> 00:15:24.682
So, you and your wife are heading to Gyeongju and Busan tomorrow, right?

00:15:25.152 --> 00:15:26.152
Yes.

00:15:26.452 --> 00:15:27.452
Here you go, sir.

00:15:36.132 --> 00:15:38.562
Provare per credere.

00:15:38.632 --> 00:15:42.302
(It's an Italian proverb meaning, "You have to try it to believe it.")

00:15:42.572 --> 00:15:44.172
When I was in the US,

00:15:44.442 --> 00:15:48.072
I had an Italian friend named Marco, and he used to say,

00:15:48.712 --> 00:15:51.042
"You have to experience it to believe it."

00:15:51.242 --> 00:15:52.782
You know what I mean, right?

00:15:53.252 --> 00:15:54.552
Of course, I do.

00:15:54.882 --> 00:15:57.252
Provare per credere!

00:15:59.592 --> 00:16:03.222
Well... It's hard to see how great our shoes are at first...

00:16:03.292 --> 00:16:05.422
just by walking around the store once,

00:16:05.422 --> 00:16:07.992
and that's why we want you to wear them...

00:16:08.062 --> 00:16:10.032
and travel in them for three days.

00:16:10.432 --> 00:16:13.502
But even after that experience,

00:16:13.502 --> 00:16:15.272
if you still think they're not right,

00:16:15.332 --> 00:16:17.672
then at least there'll be no regrets on either side.

00:16:18.342 --> 00:16:22.682
And this is the reason we're giving them to you as a gift.

00:16:26.552 --> 00:16:27.582
Very well.

00:16:28.252 --> 00:16:29.282
Wait.

00:16:30.282 --> 00:16:32.222
Your wife is going with you, right?

00:16:32.892 --> 00:16:34.022
Yes, she is.

00:16:34.392 --> 00:16:36.492
Do you know her shoe size?

00:16:37.392 --> 00:16:39.362
Provare per credere!

00:16:39.562 --> 00:16:42.202
We tried the shoes for four entire days...

00:16:42.262 --> 00:16:43.362
while on the trip.

00:16:43.632 --> 00:16:46.672
And they were incredibly comfortable...

00:16:46.732 --> 00:16:49.372
and light despite being leather.

00:16:49.972 --> 00:16:53.012
And my wife. She loved them even more.

00:16:54.272 --> 00:16:56.142
They even sent us pictures,

00:16:56.712 --> 00:17:00.252
saying they look great with jeans.

00:17:00.712 --> 00:17:01.752
They did?

00:17:02.322 --> 00:17:06.492
I hope our product is successful in Europe as well.

00:17:06.592 --> 00:17:09.722
Of course. Korean products are trusted internationally.

00:17:09.962 --> 00:17:11.192
Thank you so much.

00:17:16.902 --> 00:17:19.632
(European Franchise Agreement Signing Ceremony)

00:17:19.732 --> 00:17:22.202
(Park Jin Seok)

00:17:24.742 --> 00:17:26.542
(CEO Park Jin Seok)

